      • setParticipant

        public void setParticipant(URI participant)
                    throws SBOLValidationException
        Sets the participant property of this object to the given one.

        If this object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDocument instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        participant - the participant property of this object
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the given participant argument is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated ModuleDefinition instance is not null and given participant URI is not found in its list of FunctionalComponent instances.

      • addRole

        public boolean addRole(URI roleURI)
        Adds the given role URI to this Participation's set of role URIs.

        If this Participation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDocument instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        roleURI - the given role URI to this Participation's set of role URIs
        Returns:
        true if this set did not already contain the specified role.

      • removeRole

        public boolean removeRole(URI roleURI)
                   throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes the given role reference from the set of role references.

        If this Participation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDocument instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        roleURI - the given role reference from the set of role references.
        Returns:
        true if the matching role reference is removed successfully, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if removing the last role

      • setRoles

        public void setRoles(Set<URI> roles)
              throws SBOLValidationException
        Clears the existing set of role references first, then adds the given set of the role references to this Participation object.

        If this Participation object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDocument instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        roles - the given role reference from the set of role references to be added
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if there are no roles
